{
  "chapter": {
    "id": "rsv:job.23",
    "translationId": "rsv",
    "bookSlug": "job",
    "chapterNumber": 23,
    "referenceLabel": "Job 23",
    "summary": "Source text for Job 23 in Revised Standard Version."
  },
  "verses": [
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.23.1",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 23,
      "verseNumber": 1,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 23:1",
      "text": "Then Job answered:",
      "paragraphStart": true
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.23.2",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 23,
      "verseNumber": 2,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 23:2",
      "text": "“Today also my complaint is bitter, his hand is heavy in spite of my groaning.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.23.3",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 23,
      "verseNumber": 3,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 23:3",
      "text": "Oh, that I knew where I might find him, that I might come even to his seat!",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.23.4",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 23,
      "verseNumber": 4,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 23:4",
      "text": "I would lay my case before him and fill my mouth with arguments.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.23.5",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 23,
      "verseNumber": 5,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 23:5",
      "text": "I would learn what he would answer me, and understand what he would say to me.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.23.6",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 23,
      "verseNumber": 6,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 23:6",
      "text": "Would he contend with me in the greatness of his power? No; he would give heed to me.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.23.7",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 23,
      "verseNumber": 7,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 23:7",
      "text": "There an upright man could reason with him, and I should be acquitted for ever by my judge.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.23.8",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 23,
      "verseNumber": 8,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 23:8",
      "text": "“Behold, I go forward, but he is not there; and backward, but I cannot perceive him;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.23.9",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 23,
      "verseNumber": 9,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 23:9",
      "text": "on the left hand I seek him, but I cannot behold him; I turn to the right hand, but I cannot see him.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.23.10",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 23,
      "verseNumber": 10,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 23:10",
      "text": "But he knows the way that I take; when he has tried me, I shall come forth as gold.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.23.11",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 23,
      "verseNumber": 11,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 23:11",
      "text": "My foot has held fast to his steps; I have kept his way and have not turned aside.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.23.12",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 23,
      "verseNumber": 12,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 23:12",
      "text": "I have not departed from the commandment of his lips; I have treasured in my bosom the words of his mouth.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.23.13",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 23,
      "verseNumber": 13,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 23:13",
      "text": "But he is unchangeable and who can turn him? What he desires, that he does.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.23.14",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 23,
      "verseNumber": 14,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 23:14",
      "text": "For he will complete what he appoints for me; and many such things are in his mind.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.23.15",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 23,
      "verseNumber": 15,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 23:15",
      "text": "Therefore I am terrified at his presence; when I consider, I am in dread of him.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.23.16",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 23,
      "verseNumber": 16,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 23:16",
      "text": "God has made my heart faint; the Almighty has terrified me;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.23.17",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 23,
      "verseNumber": 17,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 23:17",
      "text": "for I am hemmed in by darkness, and thick darkness covers my face.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    }
  ]
}
